[
    {
        "content": "<p>Let <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>Y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X,Y</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8778em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span></span></span></span> be topological spaces.<br>\nLet <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>Y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f : X \\to Y</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span></span></span></span> be a continuous function.<br>\nLet <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>τ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\tau(Y)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1132em;\">τ</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> denote the topology of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>Y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">Y</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span></span></span></span>, regarded as a poset category.</p>\n<p>Write <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>J</mi><mi>f</mi></msub><mo>:</mo><mi>τ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>→</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">p</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">J_f : \\tau(Y) \\to \\mathbf{Top}/X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.9694em;vertical-align:-0.2861em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3361em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0962em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2861em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1132em;\">τ</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">Top</span></span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> for the functor which sends the open set <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>U</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">U</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span></span></span></span> to the inclusion <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>U</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>⊂</mo><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f^{-1}(U)\\subset X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0641em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">−</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">⊂</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span>. Then the nerve-realization adjunction induced by <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>J</mi><mi>f</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">J_f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.9694em;vertical-align:-0.2861em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3361em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0962em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2861em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> between <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">h</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{Psh}(Y)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">Psh</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">p</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{Top}/X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">Top</span></span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> restricts to the familiar adjunction between <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">h</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{Sh}(Y)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">Sh</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">e</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{Etale}(X)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">Etale</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> which is usually written as the composition of the equivalance <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">h</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>≃</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">e</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{Sh}(X) \\simeq \\mathbf{Etale}(X)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">Sh</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≃</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">Etale</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> and an unrelated adjunction <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">h</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mtext>  </mtext><mo>⟺</mo><mtext>  </mtext><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">h</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{Sh}(X) \\iff \\mathbf{Sh}(Y)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">Sh</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">⟺</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">Sh</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p>I realized this recently and found it interesting. I just wanted to share this. </p>\n<p>I have written up a proof here in some personal notes.<br>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/patrick-nicodemus/research/blob/main/geometry/manifolds.typ\">https://github.com/patrick-nicodemus/research/blob/main/geometry/manifolds.typ</a>, line 192</p>\n<p>An important theorem here, somehow enabling this nice correspondence seems to be that the pullback functor <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">p</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>Y</mi><mo>→</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">p</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{Top}/Y\\to\\mathbf{Top}/X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">Top</span></span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">Top</span></span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> is cocontinuous. As a result, it preserves pointwise left Kan extensions; so the usual functor <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>τ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>→</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">p</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>Y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\tau(Y) \\to \\mathbf{Top}/Y</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1132em;\">τ</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">Top</span></span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span></span></span></span> (whose associated \"realization\" is the etale space functor for sheaves on Y) can be composed with the pullback functor to give a realization from sheaves on Y to etale spaces on X. (It is interesting that the pullback functor sends etale spaces to etale spaces.)</p>",
        "id": 565066979,
        "sender_full_name": "Patrick Nicodemus",
        "timestamp": 1766435807
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>A particular case gives you (admittedly, with a certain amount of work) </p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"424412\">Patrick Nicodemus</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/229136-theory.3A-category-theory/topic/A.20nerve-realization.20adjunction/near/565066979\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>the equivalence <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">h</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>≃</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">e</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{Sh}(X) \\simeq \\mathbf{Etale}(X)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">Sh</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≃</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">Etale</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>just choose <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>i</mi><mi>d</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f=id</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">d</span></span></span></span>!</p>",
        "id": 565197632,
        "sender_full_name": "fosco",
        "timestamp": 1766514252
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, this is something I maybe should have made more explicit: part of what makes this interesting to me is that it generalizes this nerve realization adjunction which is pretty well known.</p>",
        "id": 565198312,
        "sender_full_name": "Patrick Nicodemus",
        "timestamp": 1766514624
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This is highly unrelated and directed to French native speakers. </p>\n<p>I remember have been scolded by algebraic geometers in my alma mater because it's not supposed to be an \"etale space\" but an \"*étalé space\", accent on both e, and it makes a difference (also: étale cohomology, accent only on the first e). Is it correct? <span aria-label=\"smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"smile\">:smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 565199180,
        "sender_full_name": "fosco",
        "timestamp": 1766515141
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm not a native French speaker but I can confirm: étalé space, étale cohomology.</p>\n<p>I remember a conversation about this some time ago on this Zulip.  The general consensus, if I am not mistaken, seemed to be \"write it and pronounce it however you want\" (unless you're writing/speaking French, in which case you are obviously going to stick to the correct spelling and pronounciation).  I don't think French native speakers would disagree with this, but maybe I don't know enough algebraic geometers! <span aria-label=\"smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"smile\">:smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 565199976,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Mazza",
        "timestamp": 1766515597
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The nLab says this:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<h3>Grammar and spelling</h3>\n<p>In French, the verb 'étaler' means, roughly, to spread out; '-er' becomes '-é' to make a past participle.  So an 'espace étalé' is a space that has been spread out over <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span></span></span></span>.  On the other hand, 'étale' is a (relatively obscure, distantly related) nautical adjective that can be translated as 'calm' or 'slack'.  </p>\n<p>To quote from the <a href=\"https://fr.wiktionary.org/wiki/%C3%A9tale\">Wiktionnaire français</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>'étale' _qualifie la mer qui ne monte ni ne descend &#224; la fin du flot ou du jusant_ <br>\n('flot' = 'flow' and 'jusant' = 'ebb').</p>\n</blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia_talk:WikiProject_Mathematics/Archive11#french_spelling\">Further reference</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Pronunciation</h3>\n<p>The French pronunciation of \"étalé\" is three syllables; that of \"étale\" is two syllables, with the final \"e\" silent. Many English-speaking mathematicians follow the respective French pronunciations; see for example <a href=\"https://nforum.ncatlab.org/discussion/11283/etale-space/?Focus=84522#Comment_84522\">this nForum thread</a>.</p>\n<p>Others use the two-syllable pronunciation (corresponding to French \"étale\") for both written forms \"étale\" and \"étalé\". This group included <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/Grothendieck\">[[Grothendieck]]</a> himself, when speaking English. (See Colin McLarty, from 4:45 to 6:05 and particularly <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5AR55ZsHmKI&amp;t=326s\">at 5:26</a>.)<br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>",
